The paper discusses a compression algorithm for genomic databases, which involves parsing substrings and using relative pointers. This suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), databases (cs.DB), information theory (cs.IT), or machine learning (cs.LG). However, since the focus is on compression and efficient random access, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely categories.
